The five-year accident history:
This facility has had one accidental release subject to EPA 40 CFR Part 68 within the last five years. On 10/3/18, there was a release of approximately 9,339 pounds of anhydrous ammonia to the atmosphere from PORV 124 due to the valve lifting below the set-pressure of 12 psig.  Line pressure during the event was determined to be approximately 0.5 psig. Upon discovery the valve was isolated and closed. There were no injuries or off-site damage. Atmospheric testing downwind at the fence line verified concentrations of less than 5 ppm. Regulatory agencies and neighbors were notified but emergency response was not necessary. 

The emergency response program:
